data.chText: 无谓的激动（或忧虑、活动）；大惊小怪
data.enText: unnecessary excitement, worry or activity

data.chText: 他不声不响地按照吩咐办事。
data.enText: He does what he's told without any fuss.

data.chText: 为几英镑就那么大惊小怪的！
data.enText: All that fuss over a few pounds!

data.chText: 这是部很普通的电影——我不懂为什么就轰动一时。
data.enText: It's a very ordinary movie─I don't know what all the fuss is about (= why other people think it is so good) .

data.chText: 这完全是无谓地自寻烦恼。
data.enText: It was all a fuss about nothing .

data.chText: 我们喜欢静静举行婚礼，不大事声张。
data.enText: We'd like a quiet wedding without any fuss.

data.chText: （为小事）大吵大闹，大发牢骚
data.enText: anger or complaints about sth, especially sth that is not important

data.chText: 对不起，我为吵闹声发了这么大的牢骚。
data.enText: I'm sorry for making such a fuss about the noise.

data.chText: 每次只要我提议看望你，史蒂夫就大吵大闹。
data.enText: Steve kicks up a fuss every time I even suggest seeing you.
make a fuss of/over sb

data.chText: 关爱备至；过分爱护
data.enText: to pay a lot of attention to sb, usually to show how much you like them

data.chText: 他们对婴儿呵护备至。
data.enText: They made a great fuss of the baby.

data.chText: 这狗喜欢受到宠爱。
data.enText: The dog loves being made a fuss of.

data.chText: 瞎忙一气；过分关心（枝节小事）
data.enText: to do things, or pay too much attention to things, that are not important or necessary

data.chText: 别瞎忙活了，找点有用的事干！
data.enText: Stop fussing around and find something useful to do!

data.chText: 不要没完没了摆弄你的头发了！
data.enText: Don't fuss with your hair!

data.chText: （为小事）烦恼，忧虑
data.enText: to worry about things that are not very important

data.chText: 别瞎操心了，妈妈，一切都好。
data.enText: Don't fuss, Mum, everything is all right.
not be fussed (about sb/sth)

data.chText: 不在意；无所谓；不关心
data.enText: to not mind about sth; to not have feelings about sth

data.chText: 去那里当然好，不过我无所谓。
data.enText: It'd be good to be there, but I'm not that fussed.
fuss over sb

data.chText: 对…关爱备至；过分关心
data.enText: to pay a lot of attention to sb

example: he didn't want to make a fuss
there was a terrible flap about the theft
don't fuss too much over the grandchildren--they are quite big now

value.def: Fuss is anxious or excited behaviour which serves no useful purpose.

example.ex: I don't know what all the fuss is about...
example.tran: 我不知道为什么要这样大惊小怪的。

example.ex: He just gets down to work without any fuss.
example.tran: 他刚刚静下心来开始工作。

value.tran: 紧张不安;大惊小怪;忙乱

value.def: If you fuss, you worry or behave in a nervous, anxious way about unimportant matters or rush around doing unnecessary things.

example.ex: Carol fussed about getting me a drink...
example.tran: 卡萝尔手忙脚乱地要给我弄一杯喝的。

example.ex: My wife was fussing over the food and clothing we were going to take...
example.tran: 我太太正在忙乱地准备我们要带的食物和衣服。

example.ex: She fussed with a wisp of hair over her ear...
example.tran: 她紧张不安地拨弄耳边的一缕头发。

example.ex: A team of waiters began fussing around the table...
example.tran: 一组服务生开始围着桌子团团转。

value.tran: 紧张不安;大惊小怪;瞎忙活

value.def: If you fuss over someone, you pay them a lot of attention and do things to make them happy or comfortable.

example.ex: Auntie Hilda and Uncle Jack couldn't fuss over them enough.
example.tran: 希尔达姨妈和杰克姨父对他们宠爱有加。

value.def: If you make a fuss or kick up a fuss about something, you become angry or excited about it and complain.

example.ex: I don't know why everybody makes such a fuss about a few mosquitoes...
example.tran: 我不知道为什么大家对几只蚊子大惊小怪的。

example.ex: I kick up a fuss if my wife wants to spend time alone.
example.tran: 如果妻子想要单独呆一会儿我就会大发牢骚。

value.tran: 引起骚动;大吵大闹;大发牢骚

value.def: If you make a fuss of someone, you pay them a lot of attention and do things to make them happy or comfortable.

example.ex: When I arrived my nephews made a big fuss of me.
example.tran: 我到达的时候，侄子们围着我嘘寒问暖。

value.tran: 对…关爱备至;对…过分体贴

trans: 引起骚动;大吵大闹;大发牢骚
